16:
HUH?! WHAT DO YOU MEAN, A TOP-
SECRET SEARCH FOR THE MISSING SON 
OF AN UTRA-RICH FAMILY?!
21:
You trying to get every Tom, Dick, and 
Mary after this kid?
22:
...You know how they say talent skips 
a generation? Not for the Creoles. 
Great mages crop up in that family 
like daisies in a field.
23:
But, just a few minutes ago, the heir to 
this name poofed. Gone, without a 
trace!
27:
Ahh... The sweet smell of a case, fresh 
out of an oven!
31:
Must you compare everything to 
food?
34:
What do you think happened to the 
boy?
36:
Dunno. He might've been kidnapped... 
or worse.
48: So this is where he was last seen, but...
55: Hey, Light. Come look at these signs.
84: I will now proceed to chant a spell.
88:
O, great voice that rattles the 
mountains and shakes the plains! 
Speak, and let the path before me be 
opened!
95: Yes! Just like I was taught!
99:
Hey... You, uh, wouldn't happen to be the 
missing kid... would you?
110: And you weren't trapped or hurt...
122:
My tutor said monsters drop gems 
when you beat them.
125: This is worth a lot, right?
128:
So you're out here farming items? 
But why?
134:
Haven't you heard? 
The Creoles are bankrupt.
145: Don't worry. I've got it all under control.
147:
I heard that the Guild's got sacks of 
gold... waiting for adventurers that can 
take the danger.
149:
Give me a hundred of your hardest quests! 
Should be enough to buy the manor 
back.
163: All right, I'll keep an eye on him...
168:
Wait, you're gonna help me? For free?! 
Thanks, mister!
170:
Watch out, world! 'Cause the Creoles 
are coming back!
